Creating a dark, high contrast theme in CSS involves defining a color palette that is easy on the eyes and provides good contrast between elements. Here's a simple example of how you can achieve a dark, high contrast theme using CSS:

```css
body {
    background-color: #121212; /* Dark background color */
    color: #ffffff; /* Light text color for high contrast */
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif; /* Choose a font that's easy on the eyes */
}

h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
    color: #ffa500; /* Vibrant color for headings */
}

a {
    color: #add8e6; /* Light blue for links */
    text-decoration: none; /* Remove underline */
}

a:hover {
    color: #ffa500; /* Change color on hover */
}

button {
    background-color: #ffa500; /* Button background color */
    color: #121212; /* Button text color */
    border: none; /* Remove border */
    padding: 10px 20px; /* Padding for button */
    text-align: center; /* Center text */
    text-decoration: none; /* Remove underline */
    display: inline-block; /* Make it inline */
    font-size: 16px; /* Button text size */
    margin: 4px 2px; /* Margin around button */
    cursor: pointer; /* Change cursor on hover */
    border-radius: 5px; /* Rounded corners */
}

button:hover {
    background-color: #add8e6; /* Change background color on hover */
}
```

This CSS will give you a dark background with high contrast text and elements. The colors are chosen to provide good contrast and are easy on the eyes. You can adjust the colors to your liking, or use a color scheme generator to find a palette that works for you.
